 BY MAYOWA SAMUEL Professor (Princess) Taibah Danmole, the first child of late Oba Jimoh Oyewumi, Soun of Ogbomoso who passed on 29 days ago, has also died. Reports said a family source disclosed that Danmole died on Saturday evening in Ilorin after battling with a sickness for close to a year. Her death came a few days to the 40th day Fidau prayer for her late father who reigned for 48 years as Soun of Ogbomoso. Until her death, Danmole was a Professor of Science Education at the Lagos State University and governing council member at Al-Hikmah University, Ilorin. The late professor served between 2008 and 2010 and between 2016 and 2019 as the Head of Department of Science Education in LASU before she was elevated to the Professorial in 2016. The late one time Commissioner in Oyo State was expected to be buried on Sunday afternoon in Ilorin. 